INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_2035_L092$$, 2026, $$Base Expeditionary Targeting Surveillance System - Combined (BETSS-C) (BZ6501) is a family of force protection surveillance systems providing 24/7, 360-degree visual coverage with a tower- or tripod-
 mounted EO/IR (electro-optical/infra-red) Sensor payload that offers detection ranges out to 20km. The system utilizes the Ageon Command and Control (C2) software and provides real-time video for 24/7,
 365 continuous video feeds. The trailer-mounted Persistent Surveillance System - Ground (PSS-G) sensor platform is available in both an 80' heavy tower and a 25' medium tower. Alternatively, the smaller
 Cerberus Lite Scout and Detachable Kits are mounted on tripods for expeditionary applications. These systems utilize long range detection sensors that benefit from the elevation of the parent platforms for
 increased line of sight. All BETSS-C system variants can be equipped with wireless C2 capabilities.

 Justification:
 FY 2027 procurement dollars in the amount of $1.818 million supports the procurement of four (4) Base Expeditionary Targeting Surveillance Systems - Combined (BETSS-C), Persistent Surveillance System -
 Ground (PSS-G) Heavy towers and associated cabling and mounting hardware. This requirement is the result of End-of-Life (EOL) and operational safety issues due to system age and corrosion brought about
 by current fielded environment in support of Operation Inherent Resolve (OIR).

 In accordance with section 1815 of the FY 2008 National Defense Authorization Act (P.L. 110 - 181), this item is necessary for use by the active and reserve components of the Armed Forces for homeland
 defense missions, domestic emergency responses, and providing military support to civil authorities.$$, $$$$, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Army                                                                                                                            Date: April 2026
