INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_2035_L096$$, 2026, $$The FY 2026 spend plan amount for AD0500 / COUNTER SMALL UNMANNED AERIAL SYSTEM (C-SUAS) includes $335,568 thousands of discretionary and $260,440 thousands of mandatory (reconciliation)
 for a total of $596,008 thousands.

 The C-sUAS system-of-systems provides a modular architecture of expeditionary and mobile platforms, sensors, effectors, electronic warfare technology, and electro-optical/infrared components, supported by a
 joint, interoperable fire control system. Funds support the procurement, training, and equipping of fixed, semi-fixed, mounted, dismounted, and handheld counter-UAS capabilities for U.S. forces and strategically
 important Department of War (DoW) facilities worldwide.

 In May 2024, multiple C-sUAS programs were approved for entry into the Major Capability Acquisition (MCA) pathway at post-Full Rate Production (FRP). Enduring programs are required to develop, test,
 evaluate, and continuously integrate solutions, to address a rapidly emerging UAS threat that continues to grow in sophistication, range, lethality, and numbers.$$, $$$$, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Army                                                                                                                             Date: April 2026
