 Description:
 The FY 2026 spend plan amount for Production Base Support (OTH) includes $0 of discretionary and $249,000 thousand of mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of $249,000 thousand.

 Funds key investments from the Army's Organic Industrial Base (OIB) Modernization Implementation Plan at Blue Grass Army Depot (BGAD), Rock Island Arsenal (JMTC), Anniston Army Depot (ANAD),
 Tobyhanna Army Depot (TYAD), and Letterkenny Army Depot (LEAD), alongside enterprise-wide initiatives for all Government-Owned, Government-Operated (GOGO) facilities.
 The FY 2027 investment prioritizes digital transformation, advanced manufacturing, microelectronics, and infrastructure upgrades to enhance operational efficiency, readiness, and innovation across the Army
 Organic Industrial Base (OIB). Key efforts include expanding digital tools, securing industrial control networks, advancing unmanned systems capabilities, embedding distributed 3D printing, enabling forward-
 deployed repair capabilities, scaling microelectronics production, and modernizing component remanufacturing facilities through equipment purchases. These initiatives address critical sustainment challenges,
 improve throughput, and support the Army's modernization and readiness objectives.

 This line item includes the following major projects: Digital Transformation, Industrial Control Network (ICN) Completion, Component Remanufacturing Facility (CRF) Equipment, Advanced Manufacturing / Non-
 Recurring Engineering, MicroElectronics (ME) Upgrades, the OIB Innovation Hub, and Forward Repair Equipment.
