 Description:
 This program, P-3A Mod 8629C17, LARGE AIRCRAFT INFRARED COUNTERMEASURES C-17, is a new start.
 The Large Aircraft Infrared Countermeasures (LAIRCM) system provides a significantly improved defensive capability for the Department of War to counter infrared (IR) man-portable air defense systems
 (MANPADS) and surface-to-air missile (SAM) threats by detecting, tracking, and countering incoming IR missiles.

 This system is fully autonomous following power-up and consists of Group A aircraft modification kits and Group B hardware. The current LAIRCM system configuration consists of missile warning sensors
 (MWS), a laser transmitter assembly, control interface unit and processors to detect, track, jam and counter incoming missiles.

 LAIRCM enhancements and retrofits to the current configuration are planned for purchase and installation from FY16 and beyond. These enhancements include retrofits to upgrade the entire C-17 fleet to the
 LAIRCM Block 30 configuration. Starting in FY27 LAIRCM Block 35 kits will be purchased that provide updates using new technology that advance the system capability, address diminishing manufacturing
 sources (DMS), reliability improvement efforts, and Life of Type Buys (LTB). LAIRCM Blk 35 Group B installs will begin in FY2029.

 The "Change Orders" line in the funding table includes DMS costs for the identification, review, and monitoring of items with high DMS risk potential, classification of identified items according to criticality,
 identification of alternatives for items having high DMS risks, and non-recurring engineering (NRE)/replacement cost for DMS components. Additionally, "change orders" include NRE/replacement costs for
 equipment updates to increase reliability, availability, and maintainability of LAIRCM Group B components as identified during the fiscal year.

 Block 30 to Block 35 Transition: Block 35 will require the purchase of the new Laser Turret Assembly, software updates, installation of the LRU which is expected to be done organically by maintainers, and
 certification on the platform, to include airworthiness activities and technical order updates. Funding may be used to support any NRE efforts and testing required to support Block 35.


 Milestone/Development Status

 Development is complete.
