 average age of 32 years and began reaching their extended service life in 2015. It will replace legacy LCAC capacity in enabling the rapid response of the Amphibious Ready Group and Marine Expeditionary
 Unit operations.

 The SSC is an aluminum air-cushion vehicle (hovercraft) designed to enhance the Navy and Marine Corps' capability to execute a broad spectrum of missions from humanitarian assistance to major combat. Its
 primary role is to efficiently transport weapon systems, equipment, cargo, and personnel of the Marine Air/Ground Task Force. As a high-speed, amphibious craft, it projects power by being fully compatible with
 all allied amphibious ships, while performing assaults and operational maneuvers from ship to shore and across the beach.

