INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1810_L017$$, 2026, $$Funding in this P-1 line provides for the procurement of tactical Hull, Mechanical and Electrical (HM&E) equipment that will be installed aboard ships and in the facilities at the TRIDENT Refit Facility (TRF), Navy
 Intermediate Maintenance Facility (IMF) and TRIDENT Training Facility (TTF). TRF and Navy IMF are dedicated shore support facilities providing a full range of industrial support. TTF provides realistic training
 experience in operating and maintaining shipboard equipment for the OHIO Class (SSBN/SSGN) Submarines crews. SSBN/SSGN Submarines operate with two separate crews and TTF is critical in maintaining
 proficiency and certification for continued at-sea operations when not underway.

 The magnitude of this funding line is driven by the operational need for modernization and safety alterations. Funding in FY27 supports Strategic Weapons Support Systems (SWSS) Replacement of Hull Keel
 Depth Transducers for modernization of OHIO Class Hovering and Compensation Systems and modernization of the Missile Dehumidification and Drying Machine. Funding in FY27 also provides additional
 funding for Passive Fire Protection to wrap Missile Tubes on an additional hull in order to mitigate the potential impact caused by a Missile Compartment Thermal Event. FY27 also funds TRIDENT Load List
 Range/Depth Additions and Extended Refit Period (ERP) Long Lead Time Material procurements to support SSBN 741's ERP. HM&E Modernization funding enables PMS396 to respond to fleet requests for
 HM&E modernization for safety and reliability alterations.

 Funding allows for continued operation and increased supportability of systems, such as Obsolete Equipment Replacement for Ship Control Subsystem upgrades, Life Support Systems upgrades, Torpedo Tube
 Fiber Optic Interface Upgrade, SSBN TRIDENT Planned Equipment Replacement Program (TRIPER) Obsolescence, SSBN Emergency Diesel Generator (EDG), EDG Rotatable Pool program, and Emergency
 Diesel Generator Control Panel (DGCP).

 Funding in this P-1 line also provides funding for Non-Propulsion Electronics Equipment (NPES) that will be installed aboard TRIDENT Class submarines as part of the Obsolete Equipment Replacement (OER)
 Program. Beginning in FY25, all requirements are re-aligned under Budget Line Item 0950 due to the zero-sum transfer of funds from Budget Line Item 2676 into 0950. OER Program is the replacement of
 existing hardware/software that, though functional, has become operationally obsolete, is no longer in production or supportable with spare parts, or has a high failure rate making them no longer cost effective
 to maintain. OER hardware/software changes are expected to provide significant cost savings via reduced maintenance costs and use Commercial-Off-The-Shelf (COTS) technology wherever possible as long
 as all technical requirements are met. This funding line includes performance of the required fully integrated system level testing and certification of changes to the TRIDENT Combat systems prior to installation
 of the changes on the ship. Integrated testing and certification provide assurance that when the changes are installed in the ship, the TRIDENT Combat system will operate as designed, allowing the ships to
 maintain their operational schedules and mission capabilities.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
