 Description:
 The Medium Unmanned Surface Vessel Family of Systems (MUSV FoS) will ensure a suite of USV capability is delivered to the warfighter. There is an Urgent Operational Need (UON) that was validated by the
 Navy in August 2025 that requires a specific number of MUSVs by FY 2027. The Navy developed the USV Family of Systems (USV FoS) acquisition strategy in early 2026 to provide a comprehensive approach
 to delivering surface unmanned systems to warfighter at speed and scale. The USV FoS acquisition strategy is aligned to multiple theater priorities and there are urgent demand signals from the Fleet.

 MUSVs will be designed to employ modular payloads aligned with the CNO's Containerized Capabilities Campaign Plan, enabling the same containers to be fielded across the Fleet on existing platforms to
 deliver tailored offsets in accordance with the US Navy Fighting Instructions in support of the Golden Fleet initiatives. The MUSV is a foundational element of the Golden Fleet strategy, designed to work in
 concert with manned warships to increase battlespace awareness and distributed lethality. Central to this concept is the command and control (C2) relationship between manned and unmanned platforms. The
 program envisions guided-missile frigates (FF(X)) acting as a "quarterback," exercising direct C2 over large flotillas of MUSVs. This allows the frigate to extend its sensor and engagement reach significantly,
 leveraging the MUSVs as a distributed, forward-deployed extension of its own combat systems.

 Being a part of the Battleship flexible command-and-control ship set for both manned and unmanned systems, MUSV's can be led in a Surface Action Group, integrate with a Carrier Strike Group, or operate
 autonomously to secure critical sea lanes. By utilizing RAS C2 through use of Navy warfare system programs of record including BBG(X) Integrated Combat System (ICS), communications systems, and design
 reservations dedicated to future RAS C2 systems.

 The MUSV FoS will ensure competitive prototyping produces commercial-based vessel design integrated with platform machinery and autonomy software providing next-generation capabilities that align with
 Future Surface Combatant Force (FSCF).

 USV capabilities are being developed incrementally as technologies mature, ensuring efficient and affordable execution. MUSV FoS will focus on improving producibility by being non-exquisite, modular, and
 expanding competition with multiple vendors.

 The FY 2027 request for Medium Unmanned Surface Vehicle (MUSVs) includes $121,130 thousand of discretionary to acquire two vehicles and $50,000 thousand of mandatory for one additional vehicle for a
 total of $171,130 thousand and three vehicles. FY 2027 mandatory funds continue efforts from FY 2026 for continued vehicle procurement.




