INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1810_L047$$, 2027, $$Funding for LI 3501 Cryptologic Carry-On Program (CCOP) has been realigned into LI 2360 Shipboard Information Warfare (IW) as part of Other Procurement, Navy Line Item-Consolidation starting in FY 2026.
 This effort consolidates the existing number of PEs/BLIs identified by BSOs and FMB to group technology projects to allow flexibility that would foster innovation and promote efficiency. PE/BLI consolidation
 meets the DoW Implementation Plan from the Commission on PPBE Interim Report.

 The Shipboard Information Warfare (IW) budget supports Ships Signal Exploitation Equipment (SSEE) Increment F, its variants, and Engineering Change Proposals (ECP) to maintain pace with modernization
 and signal threats; SSEE Modifications (SSEE MODS); Spectral; Integrated Communications and Data System (ICADS) Increments II and III; Real Time Spectrum Operations (RTSO); Horizon; Distributed
 Operations (DO); Advanced IW Antennas (AIWA); Cryptologic Carry-On-Program (CCOP); Snakehead, and Pacific Fleet Urgent Operational Need (PACFLT UON). The SSEE Family of Systems (FoS) includes
 variants which introduce scalability and configuration modularity through a permanently installed SSEE systems and Topside Infrastructure (Topside Antennas) supplemented with mission modules to meet
 platform mission requirements for Over the Horizon Targeting (OTH-T), and Counter-Command, Control, Computing, Communications, Cyber, Intelligence, Surveillance, Reconnaissance and Targeting (C-
 C5ISRT). Mission module and ECP capabilities integrated into the SSEE Systems will enable maritime power projection by providing surface vessels the ability to disrupt, deny, degrade and defeat adversary
 (state and non-state) use of radio frequency spectrum, improving the Fleet's ability to communicate and operate therein.

 As part of the National Security Agency's (NSA) "Secure the Network" & "Secure the Enterprise" initiatives, NSA and C10F (10th Fleet) requires all systems, including U.S. Navy Surface Cryptologic Systems to
 migrate to NSAnet.

 The CCOP procures state-of-the-art, commercial off-the-shelf Signals Intelligence (SIGINT) equipment (hardware and software) in response to combatant commander requirements for a quick-reaction surface
 cryptologic carry-on capability. The equipment is procured in accordance with requirements detailed in the shipboard Information Warfare / Cryptologic System Operational Requirements Document and specific
 execution year fleet requirements. These requirements are defined by Fleet Cyber Command (FCC)/Commander TENTH Fleet (C10F) Fleet Signals Development Working Group (FSDWG), in concert with
 Shipboard Signals Exploitation Space (SSES) programs (includes Ship's Signal Exploitation Equipment Family of Systems) to ensure synergy and seamless transition to permanently installed systems. The
 FSDWG meets to determine which signals of interest (SOI)s/Targets on the FSDWG list need to be addressed. Due to a continually changing threat environment, detailed requirements are dynamic and
 equipment procured varies each year by quantity and type. Equipment suites can be configured for many targets and tasking. Target specific subsystems can either operate as stand-alone within the cryptologic
 spaces or as an add-on to existing equipment. Hardware procurements includes: receivers, recorders, tactical computers and related peripherals, antennas, electronic-warfare support measures systems,
 precision geolocation equipment, advanced signal and search equipment including spectrum analyzers and associated portable special intelligence communications equipment. CCOP equipment is installed
 as an augment to cryptologic capabilities on surface units. There are approximately 120 cryptologic capable surface ships and shore sites in the current Navy inventory. Each of these are potential users of this$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                      Date: April 2026
